----
!1. Joining Team Twine
Team Twine in Tilde Town is open to all tilde.town members who are \
interested in contributing to the team's Twine-based interactive \
fiction collaboration, the [[Team Twine Tale|http://tilde.town/~jumblesale/twine]].

All you have to do to join the team is to create a Twee file in \
your tilde.town account with your contribution and merge it into \
the Team Tale database, like this:

1. Create your Team Twine subdirectory:
<<<
{{{$ mkdir $HOME/ttitt}}}
<<<
2. Create and edit your Twee file (substitute your tilde.town user ID in the place of //user//):
<<<
{{{$ ed $HOME/ttitt/}}}//user//{{{.twee}}}
<<<
3. Enter the following sample text, and save your Twee file:
<<<
&colon;&colon; //user//-start
Once upon a time, they lived happily ever after.
<<<
4. Merge your Twee file into the Team Tale (making an alias for \
this will save typing):
<<<
{{{$ /home/jumblesale/twine/build.py}}}
<<<
5. Open the [[Team Tale web page|http://tilde.town/~jumblesale/twine]] \
in your browser. You should see a new link to your //user//-start \
passage.

Welcome to the team! You are now a member in good standing of Team \
Twine!
