----
!2. Outlining Your Tale
Now you can get that great story in your head written down and \
loaded up! This lesson explains the basics of recording and \
publishing your story as part of the Team Twine in Tilde Town Tale.

Before you start typing, it may be useful to spend some time \
thinking of your story's plot and visualizing multiple paths your \
reader/protagonist may take. In interactive fiction, the choices \
you give the reader should have consequences for how the \
protagonist's story develops, so there should be several alternate \
paths through the events of your story and several possible endings, any of which is entertaining for your reader, even if not the path or ending you conceive of as your main plot.
  
